1
00:00:00,060 --> 00:00:05,660
Characters, actions, places, occupations,
and events in this series

2
00:00:05,690 --> 00:00:08,380
are fictional and created
for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:08,440 --> 00:00:12,730
They are not intended to urge
or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:15,170
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:28,850
(Any activity I could do alone…)

6
00:00:35,820 --> 00:00:39,820
(I snapped my fingers,
and there was no more of that, Lookpeach.)

7
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:52,800
(Because anything you could do alone…)

8
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:01,900
(we could do it together.)

9
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:07,400
(Or with even more people.)

10
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:16,170
And the giant bear and the panda
lived happily ever after.

11
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:25,200
(This is more than a dream come true.)

12
00:01:33,310 --> 00:01:35,100
I just got up early to take a bath.

13
00:01:44,870 --> 00:01:46,800
We’ve been glued to each other
for almost four months.

14
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:48,500
A little time apart won’t kill us.

15
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,170
You’re wrong.

16
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,970
It’s three months and 22 days.

17
00:01:52,009 --> 00:01:53,530
-You’re still counting?
-Seven hours…

18
00:01:54,570 --> 00:01:56,259
and six minutes.

19
00:01:57,830 --> 00:01:58,800
P’Kian.

20
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:02,850
9,687,960 seconds have passed.

21
00:02:03,010 --> 00:02:04,700
Not a single one went by…

22
00:02:05,610 --> 00:02:07,600
without you in my heart.

23
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:10,400
Lookpeach.

24
00:02:10,889 --> 00:02:12,500
That’s how much I love you.

25
00:02:19,590 --> 00:02:20,540
A new tie?

26
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:22,620
What’s this?

27
00:02:23,390 --> 00:02:26,130
My heartbeat spelling out your name.

28
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:28,420
Lookpeach. Lookpeach.

29
00:02:28,460 --> 00:02:29,980
Lookpeach. Lookpeach.

30
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:34,200
Why are you wearing a suit
and tie at home?

31
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:37,250
Honestly, I like you better without a tie.

32
00:02:48,820 --> 00:02:49,800
What are you doing?

33
00:02:52,230 --> 00:02:53,620
Just take it off.

34
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:56,260
I just want to give you what you like.

35
00:02:57,020 --> 00:02:59,140
I’ll have my men throw out
every tie I own.

36
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,330
Just don’t.

37
00:03:00,710 --> 00:03:02,900
What are you going to wear
when you go back to work?

38
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,300
How about we cancel
the six-month vacation…

39
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:10,060
and make it a lifetime honeymoon instead?

40
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,610
I don’t want to spend a single day
away from my Lookpeach.

41
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:14,940
We can’t.

42
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:18,000
If we quit our jobs,
how are we supposed to make a living?

43
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,860
Actually,

44
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:23,800
if we only count my personal assets,
separate from ARSENI’s,

45
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:26,500
and live a little frugally…

46
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:30,270
say, under a billion per year…

47
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:30,890
What?

48
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,500
It might sound like a hard life,

49
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:35,250
but we should be able to get by
until we’re sixty.

50
00:03:35,460 --> 00:03:37,660
Assuming that’s the average
human lifespan.

51
00:03:38,380 --> 00:03:39,380
Totally doable, right?

52
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:45,500
And in the next life,
we’ll build a life together again.

53
00:03:45,590 --> 00:03:46,890
Gosh, P’Kian.

54
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:47,800
Oh.

55
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,300
I meant a billion for me…

56
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:54,700
and another billion for you.

57
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,340
What do you think?

58
00:03:59,290 --> 00:04:01,140
Could you live with that?

59
00:04:03,610 --> 00:04:05,400
We just go to work

60
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:07,800
then come home
to each other every evening.

61
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,900
It’s not like we’ll be apart forever.

62
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:14,700
But if we’re already together,

63
00:04:15,530 --> 00:04:16,779
why be apart at all?

64
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,100
Let the single people…

65
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:25,020
live their lonely little lives.

66
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:58,260
Rise and shine, stubborn one.

67
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:00,700
Did you reject all the pillows

68
00:06:01,770 --> 00:06:03,900
just to use my chest as one?

69
00:06:38,420 --> 00:06:39,740
What’s on the menu today, Chef?

70
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,220
Fried egg and rice,

71
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,980
served with a direct hit to your heart.

72
00:06:45,860 --> 00:06:47,500
What are you all doing up so early?

73
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,220
You cooked?

74
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:56,830
What’s the occasion?

75
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,700
3.33?

76
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,900
What’s that supposed to mean?

77
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:08,600
It’s our wedding anniversary.

78
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:11,800
3 months and 33 days.

79
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:20,600
Wouldn’t that just be
four months and three days?

80
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:25,500
How is that an anniversary?

81
00:07:26,850 --> 00:07:27,700
Everything counts.

82
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,600
It’s a nice number.

83
00:07:33,840 --> 00:07:35,900
You keep track of every little thing.

84
00:07:36,250 --> 00:07:38,000
Careful, they might just become ordinary.

85
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:46,450
The kids are here.

86
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,620
So you’re all taking Dad’s side now?

87
00:07:58,090 --> 00:08:00,700
Don’t ever say “ordinary” again.

88
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,300
It hurts, baby.

89
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,700
Aran, say that again.

90
00:08:22,970 --> 00:08:24,400
You want me to help promote a restaurant?

91
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,600
(The Italian restaurant Mr. Thee gave me.)

92
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:29,300
(Tawan came up
with the idea of renovating it.)

93
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:32,130
(It’s almost finished.
So we want to start promoting it.)

94
00:08:32,330 --> 00:08:33,400
Hmm.

95
00:08:35,429 --> 00:08:36,450
Is it going well?

96
00:08:36,549 --> 00:08:37,500
(It is.)

97
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:38,820
(While we were closed,)

98
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,700
(our regulars kept asking
when we’d reopen.)

99
00:08:42,549 --> 00:08:44,300
I meant you and Tawan.

100
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,050
How are things between you two?

101
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:54,200
He’s like a different person now.

102
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:57,500
(I can hear the smile in your voice.)

103
00:08:57,930 --> 00:09:01,180
I have Mr. Thee to thank
for giving me the restaurant.

104
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:06,100
At least I have something
to keep me busy while I’m on hiatus.

105
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:16,250
So?

106
00:09:16,650 --> 00:09:18,100
What do you say, Peach?

107
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,490
Will you do the shoot for me?

108
00:09:19,820 --> 00:09:20,870
(Think hard.)

109
00:09:20,890 --> 00:09:22,400
(I expect a good answer.)

110
00:09:23,130 --> 00:09:25,570
Actually,

111
00:09:25,660 --> 00:09:27,980
Mr. Thee and I agreed to

112
00:09:28,060 --> 00:09:30,040
take a six-month vacation
after we got married.

113
00:09:30,060 --> 00:09:32,070
Whoa! Six months?

114
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:32,900
(Yeah.)

115
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:35,970
He wants to take me
on a honeymoon trip around the world.

116
00:09:35,990 --> 00:09:37,530
We’ve already been
to more than 20 countries.

117
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:38,500
What?

118
00:09:38,570 --> 00:09:39,490
20 countries?

119
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:41,500
(Hold on, Peach.)

120
00:09:41,820 --> 00:09:43,800
(Haven’t you only been married for,
like, four months?)

121
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:45,450
Four months and three days.

122
00:09:49,060 --> 00:09:49,800
Right.

123
00:09:50,230 --> 00:09:51,200
It’s all good then.

124
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:52,100
I understand.

125
00:09:52,210 --> 00:09:53,400
(I’m really sorry.)

126
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,800
Maybe next time, Aran.

127
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,370
I don’t want to break the promise
I made to Mr. Thee.

128
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,400
(No worries.)

129
00:09:57,500 --> 00:10:00,730
Once the restaurant’s finished,
let’s have a meal together.

130
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:04,130
I’ll send you the contact info
for a photographer I know.

131
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,700
Thank you.

132
00:10:45,610 --> 00:10:46,600
What are you doing?!

133
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,700
P’Kian, what would you say if…

134
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,340
I wanted to go back to work?

135
00:10:55,410 --> 00:10:56,210
Work?

136
00:11:02,580 --> 00:11:03,500
P’Kian.

137
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:07,140
How many times must I repeat myself
before you understand?

138
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:10,180
As long as you’re under ARSENI’s roof,
you’ll never know hardship.

139
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,180
So stop thinking about going back to work.

140
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:19,450
A lone wolf finally got a taste of honey,
and it’s only been six months.

141
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,620
A whole six months.

142
00:11:20,690 --> 00:11:22,120
It’s only six full moons.

143
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,250
Is that really too long for you?

144
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:26,000
Long enough for me to almost forget
how to hold a camera.

145
00:11:26,340 --> 00:11:27,130
Perfect.

146
00:11:27,870 --> 00:11:30,620
Then you don’t miss it that much.

147
00:11:30,650 --> 00:11:31,420
P’Kian.

148
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,180
It just…

149
00:11:37,350 --> 00:11:39,500
breaks my heart
to be apart from you, Lookpeach.

150
00:11:42,980 --> 00:11:44,340
I want to get back to shooting photos.

151
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:46,850
Shoot my photos.

152
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:49,650
You’ve got the handsome and perfect model
right in front of you.

153
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:50,860
Why photograph anyone else?

154
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:51,860
It’s not the same.

155
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:52,850
How is it different?

156
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:55,700
If I wait until the six months are up,
all my connections will be gone.

157
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:57,420
Then we’ll make new ones.

158
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,530
How?

159
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:03,740
I’ll invite the whole industry
to travel the world with us.

160
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:06,000
Turn it into a networking trip.

161
00:12:06,940 --> 00:12:09,500
The whole world will be your studio.

162
00:12:09,590 --> 00:12:11,900
But we’ve already been
to more than 20 countries.

163
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:15,980
Who said our next destination
has to be a country?

164
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:16,860
Huh?

165
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,800
It’s our honeymoon, after all.

166
00:12:19,830 --> 00:12:22,260
Where do you think we should go next?

167
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,460
Don’t tell me…

168
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:30,980
Tickets to the Moon.

169
00:12:49,370 --> 00:12:50,650
P’Kian!

170
00:13:19,970 --> 00:13:21,810
It’ll just be absolute chaos.

171
00:13:35,660 --> 00:13:36,500
Ow!

172
00:13:38,330 --> 00:13:39,890
Take it seriously, P’Kian.

173
00:13:39,950 --> 00:13:41,100
You’re holding back.

174
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,870
How will I handle a real opponent
if you keep going easy on me?

175
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,100
I told you,

176
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:47,220
under my protection,

177
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:48,800
you’ll always be safe.

178
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:52,940
What are you,
the amnesiac heroine in a soap opera?

179
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:53,700
Ow!

180
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:55,600
I know you can protect me,

181
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:57,740
but I want to be able to protect
myself too.

182
00:13:58,190 --> 00:13:59,500
Now take it seriously.

183
00:14:00,140 --> 00:14:02,890
Maybe I love you too much.

184
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,050
I treasure you more than anything.

185
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:08,240
I just can’t bring myself
to throw you to the mat.

186
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:08,870
Whatever.

187
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,300
If you won’t take this seriously,

188
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:12,100
I’ll find a new sparring partner.

189
00:14:13,710 --> 00:14:14,380
You can’t.

190
00:14:14,410 --> 00:14:15,460
Why not?

191
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,700
I’d be jealous.

192
00:14:18,970 --> 00:14:20,180
Jealous of what?

193
00:14:20,410 --> 00:14:21,660
It’s just a sparring partner.

194
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,260
How could I let someone else
hold you like this?

195
00:14:25,830 --> 00:14:27,600
Just seeing people look at you

196
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,600
makes me want to gouge their eyes out.

197
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:31,800
Imagine them holding you like I am.

198
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:35,300
They wouldn’t live to tell the tale.

199
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,890
But if you’re not taking this seriously,
I’ll really find a new sparring partner.

200
00:14:41,510 --> 00:14:42,100
I’m sorry.

201
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:43,200
One, two, three.

202
00:14:46,370 --> 00:14:47,300
Did I hurt you?

203
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:48,980
I’m sorry.

204
00:14:50,020 --> 00:14:51,400
Was I too rough?

205
00:14:51,830 --> 00:14:52,770
I lost.

206
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:57,400
But my heart nearly shattered.

207
00:15:16,650 --> 00:15:17,420
Nailed it.

208
00:15:19,350 --> 00:15:20,310
Got a great teacher.

209
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:21,500
Not a teacher.

210
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:23,900
More like a husband.

211
00:15:28,990 --> 00:15:30,530
What? What’s with that look?

212
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,000
I’m really your husband,

213
00:15:33,210 --> 00:15:34,820
reserving you for eternity.

214
00:15:38,010 --> 00:15:41,580
This man was born just to love you.

215
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,300
Whoa, whoa~

216
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:58,300
Sneaking up behind me like that,
aren’t you afraid it’ll go off?

217
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:02,700
If you shoot me,
I’ll die without a single regret.

218
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:09,020
But I will go to prison for murder.

219
00:16:10,220 --> 00:16:13,540
More importantly,
I can’t live without you.

220
00:16:21,360 --> 00:16:22,600
Don’t say that.

221
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:26,300
Because death is the only thing
I can’t outrun.

222
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:30,180
But don’t worry, Lookpeach.

223
00:16:30,230 --> 00:16:31,700
If I leave this world first,

224
00:16:33,020 --> 00:16:35,020
I’ll wait for you somewhere
in the Milky Way.

225
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:38,800
There are millions of planets
in the Milky Way.

226
00:16:39,050 --> 00:16:40,500
How will we ever find each other?

227
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:42,700
We will.

228
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:45,820
But before that…

229
00:16:47,590 --> 00:16:48,900
there’s something I need to tell you.

230
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:58,100
Don’t lose yourself

231
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:01,180
just to make me happy.

232
00:17:02,810 --> 00:17:03,500
Hey.

233
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,950
You want to go back to work,
don’t you, Lookpeach?

234
00:17:19,890 --> 00:17:21,700
Why did you ask me that, P’Kian?

235
00:17:28,050 --> 00:17:31,220
I’ll send you the contact info
for a photographer I know.

236
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:49,960
KEY VISUAL SHOOT INQUIRY
MAGAZINE COVER SHOOT

237
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:54,890
MY APOLOGIES. I’M NOT TAKING PROJECTS
UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE.

238
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,020
A falling leaf hasn’t even touched
the ground yet,

239
00:18:08,210 --> 00:18:09,900
and we’re already about to be apart.

240
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,600
P’Kian, we agreed on six months.

241
00:18:13,130 --> 00:18:14,700
Let’s stick to our promise.

242
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,420
But I’m the one…

243
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:25,900
breaking my promise.

244
00:18:29,080 --> 00:18:31,220
I might be pretty busy with work,

245
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:33,130
but I promise I’ll take good care of you.

246
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:35,710
Whatever you want to do,
wherever you want to go, just tell me.

247
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:36,900
I’ll make it happen.

248
00:18:36,990 --> 00:18:38,600
If you like working,
I won’t get in your way.

249
00:18:38,630 --> 00:18:40,200
I’ll let you live your life.

250
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:42,170
How long will this honeymoon phase last?

251
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,420
For as long as I breathe.

252
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:58,700
I never forget the promises I make to you.

253
00:18:59,060 --> 00:19:00,700
And I’ll keep them.

254
00:19:02,030 --> 00:19:03,700
Every single one of them.

255
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,300
You don’t have to do that much for me.

256
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,490
Actually…

257
00:19:11,530 --> 00:19:13,400
I’ve been thinking about it for a while.

258
00:19:15,770 --> 00:19:17,820
Now that Aran’s offered you a job,

259
00:19:17,910 --> 00:19:21,700
I think it’s time I did something.

260
00:19:23,530 --> 00:19:24,700
Thank you.

261
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,580
It’s because…

262
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:40,300
I’ve finally got a grip, Lookpeach.

263
00:19:43,670 --> 00:19:46,970
Say goodbye to the over-the-top mafia boss
you used to know.

264
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,530
So, when does Aran need you?

265
00:19:52,720 --> 00:19:54,240
If you don’t mind,
could you give me just a few—

266
00:19:54,260 --> 00:19:55,640
He wants me to start immediately.

267
00:19:55,670 --> 00:19:57,380
The day after tomorrow, if possible.

268
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,900
(Seriously, Peach?)

269
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:21,200
He said he wanted to keep the promise
he made to me.

270
00:20:23,050 --> 00:20:24,890
He knows how much I like to work,
so he’s letting me go back.

271
00:20:24,940 --> 00:20:25,600
(Ah!)

272
00:20:25,620 --> 00:20:29,400
He also said I’m his heart.

273
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:32,730
He doesn’t want me
to lose myself for his sake.

274
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:34,930
How sweet is that?

275
00:20:51,260 --> 00:20:55,600
Why don’t you just ask Mr. Peach
for a little more time, sir?

276
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:56,870
Tell him you’re not ready.

277
00:20:58,100 --> 00:21:00,620
A man keeps his word.

278
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:03,300
Once he gives it, he stands by it.

279
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:05,300
Stand tall and face the consequences.

280
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:07,580
But if you’re really not okay with this—

281
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:11,260
I knew this day would come.

282
00:21:11,990 --> 00:21:13,900
I just never imagined it’d hurt…

283
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,700
hurt me this deeply.

284
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:51,580
What’s wrong?

285
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:54,460
What’s that look?

286
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:57,100
Nothing.

287
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,900
I’m perfectly fine.

288
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:01,400
Totally.

289
00:22:03,020 --> 00:22:04,400
Should we turn off the light?

290
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:06,500
Mm.

291
00:22:13,790 --> 00:22:14,600
Wait.

292
00:22:15,690 --> 00:22:17,600
Can I stock up on hugs in advance?

293
00:22:18,870 --> 00:22:20,810
You’re going back to work
the day after tomorrow, right?

294
00:22:32,260 --> 00:22:34,130
Actually, I just got off the phone
with Aran.

295
00:22:34,230 --> 00:22:35,780
I have to check out the location tomorrow.

296
00:22:35,810 --> 00:22:36,600
Huh?

297
00:22:37,220 --> 00:22:37,860
Tomorrow?

298
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:38,700
Sweet dreams.

299
00:22:38,860 --> 00:22:40,100
I love you, P’Kian.

300
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:47,900
I… I love you too.

301
00:23:08,590 --> 00:23:10,810
P’Kian, when are you going back to work?

302
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:16,000
The day my heart is strong enough.

303
00:23:21,020 --> 00:23:22,300
Can you not go, pwease?

304
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:25,300
Is it too late to change your mind?

305
00:23:27,260 --> 00:23:28,700
Don’t be such a baby.

306
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,820
Or do you want to come to work
with me today?

307
00:23:36,750 --> 00:23:37,600
It’s okay.

308
00:23:38,670 --> 00:23:42,630
Let’s leave a little room
in our hearts to miss each other.

309
00:23:43,540 --> 00:23:44,600
Then let go.

310
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:08,400
Wear my perfume today,

311
00:24:10,120 --> 00:24:11,900
so it’ll feel like I’m always with you.

312
00:24:18,270 --> 00:24:20,500
Just pray my heart doesn’t shatter

313
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:23,220
before you make it home.

314
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:39,300
Mongkol,

315
00:24:40,480 --> 00:24:43,600
tell me the good things
about long-distance relationships.

316
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:45,320
(The good thing about being apart)

317
00:24:45,340 --> 00:24:49,000
(is that it makes you
miss each other in full force.)

318
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:53,800
(It makes your reunion
feel even more special.)

319
00:24:54,070 --> 00:24:57,400
(You can tell me how long
you’ll be apart from your partner,)

320
00:24:57,550 --> 00:25:00,700
(I’ll give you more tailored advice.)

321
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:03,820
Maybe… eight hours.

322
00:25:04,040 --> 00:25:09,020
(Eight hours would not normally be
considered a long-distance relationship.)

323
00:25:12,950 --> 00:25:14,000
Don’t worry.

324
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:16,900
I’ll take good care of our children
while you’re away.

325
00:25:21,740 --> 00:25:23,600
We’ll be half a world apart,

326
00:25:24,890 --> 00:25:27,100
but I hope our hearts stay close.

327
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:30,580
I’m only going to Bang Na.

328
00:25:30,770 --> 00:25:32,020
That’s hardly half a world away.

329
00:25:36,530 --> 00:25:39,000
You two, take good care of Dad.

330
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:39,800
Of course.

331
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:42,620
Mork and I
will take good care of Dad for you.

332
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,500
Don’t worry, Mr. Peach.

333
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,000
Leave everything here to me.

334
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:51,380
Mr. Mok. What a pleasant surprise.

335
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:54,130
Just so you know,

336
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:58,370
ARSENI has a strict no-rehire policy.

337
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:00,650
Mr. Thee…

338
00:26:00,670 --> 00:26:02,340
How did that mad dog Rome

339
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:05,000
ever let his prey slip away?

340
00:26:06,570 --> 00:26:08,100
Still got him in my jaws.

341
00:26:08,610 --> 00:26:09,940
What kind of fool would let him slip away?

342
00:26:11,590 --> 00:26:12,700
-Uncle Rome.
-Uncle Rome.

343
00:26:33,510 --> 00:26:35,460
Mr. Thee, the team told me you’d…

344
00:26:35,490 --> 00:26:36,300
Ahem.

345
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,700
I only asked you for one thing,

346
00:26:39,950 --> 00:26:41,400
and you still can’t do it?

347
00:26:44,890 --> 00:26:46,940
Thee, the team told me—

348
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:47,380
Ahem!

349
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:51,330
My dear friend Mok,

350
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,500
fix the way you address me,

351
00:26:54,370 --> 00:26:55,380
or I’ll have Rome…

352
00:26:55,750 --> 00:26:57,870
deal with you for every word
you get wrong.

353
00:26:59,350 --> 00:27:00,020
Mr. Thee.

354
00:27:01,040 --> 00:27:01,980
That’s one.

355
00:27:03,910 --> 00:27:04,700
Dude.

356
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:06,620
Let’s go with ‘dude,’ sir.

357
00:27:16,580 --> 00:27:17,580
Keep going,

358
00:27:18,860 --> 00:27:19,500
bud.

359
00:27:25,930 --> 00:27:27,220
The ARSENI team told me

360
00:27:29,690 --> 00:27:33,660
you, my dude, cut your vacation short

361
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,700
and you’re coming back early.

362
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:40,140
That’s right, buddy.

363
00:27:40,240 --> 00:27:41,000
But…

364
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:43,100
ARSENI Hong Kong

365
00:27:43,780 --> 00:27:45,220
still hasn’t found you a new assistant.

366
00:27:47,340 --> 00:27:49,400
So I volunteered to help
cover that for you,

367
00:27:50,630 --> 00:27:51,530
buddy,

368
00:27:52,990 --> 00:27:54,200
until then.

369
00:27:59,830 --> 00:28:02,530
How self-centered.
Always get everyone dancing to your tune.

370
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:06,460
Did I ever so much as utter a word
asking you to come back?

371
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:08,200
Damn it, Kian.

372
00:28:16,290 --> 00:28:17,780
Please, don’t fight.

373
00:28:18,730 --> 00:28:19,600
Let’s do this.

374
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:21,600
I’ll look after you, dude,

375
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,400
until we find you a new assistant, sir.

376
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:26,620
As for you, Mr. Rome,

377
00:28:27,980 --> 00:28:29,400
we’ll stay here with them.

378
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:31,580
It’s settled.

379
00:28:49,770 --> 00:28:50,700
Hey.

380
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:52,900
You really don’t want to get paid?

381
00:28:52,990 --> 00:28:54,100
It’s fine, Aran.

382
00:28:55,180 --> 00:28:57,100
I haven’t touched a camera in months.

383
00:28:58,100 --> 00:29:00,800
This is good practice for me.

384
00:29:03,390 --> 00:29:05,600
It’s Mr. Peachayarat Lee after all.

385
00:29:06,330 --> 00:29:07,900
He only works to socialize, huh?

386
00:29:10,140 --> 00:29:11,600
So how are you?

387
00:29:12,130 --> 00:29:13,340
How’s married life?

388
00:29:13,680 --> 00:29:14,500
Good.

389
00:29:16,010 --> 00:29:17,230
Actually, I think…

390
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:18,700
it’s really good.

391
00:29:23,380 --> 00:29:24,600
I think

392
00:29:25,580 --> 00:29:28,600
it’s filling something
I was missing in my life.

393
00:29:30,340 --> 00:29:31,620
I don’t need anything else now.

394
00:29:35,660 --> 00:29:36,850
I wake up next to him.

395
00:29:37,700 --> 00:29:39,100
I go to bed beside him.

396
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:41,850
We eat every meal together.

397
00:29:45,230 --> 00:29:46,600
You’ve changed a lot.

398
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:50,000
I haven’t changed.

399
00:29:50,370 --> 00:29:51,400
I’m just

400
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:53,670
experiencing something I never had before.

401
00:29:55,630 --> 00:29:56,820
Yeah, yeah.

402
00:29:56,950 --> 00:29:58,500
Why are you asking?

403
00:29:59,350 --> 00:30:00,460
Thinking about getting married?

404
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:01,660
Oh, come on.

405
00:30:03,020 --> 00:30:04,500
I’ve never even thought about it.

406
00:30:04,870 --> 00:30:06,000
Still not sure?

407
00:30:13,710 --> 00:30:14,600
I don’t know.

408
00:30:15,690 --> 00:30:16,900
Maybe I’m still young.

409
00:30:17,170 --> 00:30:18,700
I haven’t really thought that far ahead.

410
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,660
Are you calling me old?

411
00:30:20,870 --> 00:30:23,780
I didn’t. You did.

412
00:30:23,890 --> 00:30:24,800
Come on, Aran.

413
00:30:26,170 --> 00:30:27,310
I’m not shooting for you anymore.

414
00:30:27,650 --> 00:30:28,860
Easy, easy.

415
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:30,000
That looks good.

416
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,320
Nice try changing the subject.

417
00:30:32,340 --> 00:30:33,700
Need anything else, Mr. Peach?

418
00:30:34,670 --> 00:30:35,800
Thanks, Tawan.

419
00:30:36,750 --> 00:30:38,200
If you need anything, let me know.

420
00:30:39,710 --> 00:30:40,600
Uh…

421
00:30:41,570 --> 00:30:43,200
Move it a little to the left.

422
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,110
Thanks.

423
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:58,870
Why are you smiling?

424
00:30:58,890 --> 00:31:00,400
-What?
-Why are you smiling?

425
00:31:00,730 --> 00:31:01,700
No reason.

426
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:06,600
I’m just proud.

427
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,300
He’s my trainee.

428
00:31:09,680 --> 00:31:13,000
So he’s been promoted
from roommate to trainee, huh?

429
00:31:13,470 --> 00:31:14,200
Peach!

430
00:31:16,070 --> 00:31:17,100
Just keep shooting.

431
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:20,900
Tawan’s proven himself
time and time again.

432
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:23,250
When are you finally going to give in?

433
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:27,640
My heart’s already softened.
It’s practically melted.

434
00:31:30,420 --> 00:31:31,200
But I don’t know.

435
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:34,910
Things are so good right now.

436
00:31:36,940 --> 00:31:39,400
So good I don’t even
want to move forward or backward.

437
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:00,400
You got fired

438
00:32:01,450 --> 00:32:03,050
with ten years’ worth of severance.

439
00:32:03,850 --> 00:32:06,000
If I were you, I’d leave everything behind

440
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:07,500
and travel the world.

441
00:32:07,630 --> 00:32:09,380
That’s an interesting suggestion.

442
00:32:12,610 --> 00:32:13,900
Leave everything behind, huh?

443
00:32:20,860 --> 00:32:23,200
Everything except me.

444
00:32:25,350 --> 00:32:26,700
If you’re the exception,

445
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:29,250
then it’s not really everything.

446
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:35,000
Make me your exception.

447
00:32:36,830 --> 00:32:37,390
Mr. Rome.

448
00:32:37,420 --> 00:32:40,800
Because you’re the exception
to every rule.

449
00:32:44,990 --> 00:32:45,960
What are you doing?

450
00:32:51,220 --> 00:32:54,200
I’m sorry for upsetting you,

451
00:32:58,150 --> 00:32:59,860
but I can’t leave Mr. Thee.

452
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:03,200
At least not for now.

453
00:33:09,930 --> 00:33:11,200
You really think…

454
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:14,300
that’s enough to make me cave?

455
00:33:39,690 --> 00:33:40,450
Thank you.

456
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:44,330
For the past two months,

457
00:33:44,520 --> 00:33:46,450
I haven’t fallen in love with you
over and over again…

458
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:50,410
because I never fell out of love with you
in the first place.

459
00:33:52,880 --> 00:33:53,600
Très bien.

460
00:34:09,290 --> 00:34:11,219
P’Kian, did you really have to do all this?

461
00:34:11,290 --> 00:34:15,699
I’m celebrating
my 99,999th beautiful minute with you.

462
00:34:16,570 --> 00:34:18,699
With every passing minute,

463
00:34:19,489 --> 00:34:23,699
my love for you only grows.

464
00:34:26,040 --> 00:34:26,900
P’Kian.

465
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:28,889
What?

466
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,699
There are so many people here.

467
00:34:32,420 --> 00:34:33,659
Anyway…

468
00:34:34,090 --> 00:34:37,620
our private rooftop is ready
for our 100,000-minute celebration.

469
00:34:56,090 --> 00:34:56,900
Dad.

470
00:34:57,390 --> 00:35:00,500
My teacher said I have a talent for art.

471
00:35:08,170 --> 00:35:09,600
Dad, you look sad.

472
00:35:09,630 --> 00:35:11,400
You’re missing Peach, aren’t you?

473
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:14,540
If you miss him, why don’t you call him?

474
00:35:41,450 --> 00:35:42,290
Hello?

475
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:45,100
Oh, Lookpeach.

476
00:35:46,890 --> 00:35:49,100
It’s not like I called
because I missed you or anything.

477
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:52,300
I’ve finally gotten a grip.

478
00:35:52,350 --> 00:35:55,500
If you didn’t miss me, then what is it?

479
00:35:59,340 --> 00:36:01,100
Marn had art class today.

480
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,100
She drew this really beautiful picture.

481
00:36:03,950 --> 00:36:05,010
Take a look.

482
00:36:06,950 --> 00:36:10,340
That blue-and-green bear is pretty cute.

483
00:36:10,550 --> 00:36:11,200
Right?

484
00:36:11,330 --> 00:36:15,820
So you called just to show me the bear?

485
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:17,300
You’re sure you don’t miss me?

486
00:36:18,570 --> 00:36:19,300
Mm.

487
00:36:20,970 --> 00:36:22,000
That’s all.

488
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:23,220
Okay.

489
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:25,060
That’s all, then.

490
00:36:25,330 --> 00:36:27,380
I’ll get back to work.

491
00:36:31,460 --> 00:36:32,530
I miss you, P’Kian.

492
00:36:52,600 --> 00:36:54,400
Wow, your photography’s amazing.

493
00:36:56,230 --> 00:36:57,170
What about you?

494
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:59,500
When are you going to model for me again?

495
00:37:02,770 --> 00:37:04,700
I broke my contract with ARSENI.

496
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,300
I’m probably blacklisted by now.

497
00:37:07,510 --> 00:37:10,540
Who would dare blacklist
the company owner’s partner’s little bro?

498
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:11,730
Wow.

499
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:12,900
What a flex.

500
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:13,860
I’m kidding.

501
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:15,060
All right.

502
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:17,330
If you’re happy with the photos,

503
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:20,500
I’ll start editing them
and upload the files later.

504
00:37:20,540 --> 00:37:21,100
Sounds good.

505
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:22,500
Let’s do that, yeah?

506
00:37:23,230 --> 00:37:24,000
Okay.

507
00:37:25,230 --> 00:37:26,000
Oh, hey.

508
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:27,700
Why don’t you stay for dinner?

509
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:28,660
It’s on the house.

510
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:31,060
I don’t think I can today.

511
00:37:31,690 --> 00:37:33,300
Someone’s waiting for me at home.

512
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:37,700
Here.

513
00:37:43,080 --> 00:37:44,180
Thank you both so much.

514
00:37:46,710 --> 00:37:47,730
LOVETHEE 1
BANGKOK

515
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:48,740
Whoa!

516
00:37:53,170 --> 00:37:55,100
Let me make it up to you.

517
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,800
Dinner’s on me.

518
00:37:56,930 --> 00:37:58,850
We can invite Mr. Thee and Lookplub too.

519
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:00,380
Call it an after-wedding dinner.

520
00:38:00,550 --> 00:38:01,660
You really don’t have to, Aran.

521
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:03,000
Yes, I do.

522
00:38:03,590 --> 00:38:05,740
We missed your wedding.

523
00:38:06,380 --> 00:38:07,880
The least I can do is treat you to a meal.

524
00:38:07,910 --> 00:38:08,900
Honestly, it’s okay.

525
00:38:09,260 --> 00:38:11,300
We kept the wedding small.

526
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:12,510
Just family.

527
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:14,400
Hold on.

528
00:38:14,830 --> 00:38:16,020
What’s that supposed to mean?

529
00:38:16,040 --> 00:38:16,970
Am I an outsider?

530
00:38:16,990 --> 00:38:19,100
You were the one who said
I’m like your little brother.

531
00:38:19,690 --> 00:38:22,900
Then I’m bringing my whole family
to your restaurant, okay?

532
00:38:23,670 --> 00:38:25,430
I should get going. See you later.

533
00:38:25,510 --> 00:38:26,620
Okay. Bye.

534
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:27,860
See you, Tawan.

535
00:38:28,140 --> 00:38:29,100
Have a good night, Mr. Peach.

536
00:38:45,010 --> 00:38:46,000
You okay?

537
00:38:46,940 --> 00:38:50,000
Seeing how kind Mr. Peach is to you

538
00:38:51,770 --> 00:38:53,200
just makes me feel even worse.

539
00:38:56,540 --> 00:38:58,100
I was such an idiot back then.

540
00:39:03,670 --> 00:39:04,900
Don’t think like that.

541
00:39:06,710 --> 00:39:08,100
No one thinks so.

542
00:39:10,810 --> 00:39:12,600
Peach isn’t angry with you anymore.

543
00:39:16,550 --> 00:39:17,700
Good boy.

544
00:39:54,630 --> 00:39:55,650
My Lookpeach.

545
00:39:56,420 --> 00:39:58,000
Look at you with that big, fat smile.

546
00:40:00,530 --> 00:40:03,800
I missed you so much,
my heart almost burst out of my chest.

547
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:07,000
Lookplub.

548
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:09,780
Why didn’t you tell me
you were coming home?

549
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:11,700
I wanted to surprise you.

550
00:40:12,280 --> 00:40:14,200
Instead, I ended up
as mosquito food out here.

551
00:40:14,460 --> 00:40:16,000
Well, I’m home now.

552
00:40:30,490 --> 00:40:31,800
Everyone’s here tonight.

553
00:40:32,000 --> 00:40:33,020
It feels warm.

554
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:36,740
How was the trip with Mr. Mok, Rome?

555
00:40:37,590 --> 00:40:38,400
It was great.

556
00:40:38,800 --> 00:40:40,200
But it ended too soon.

557
00:40:41,320 --> 00:40:42,530
We got called back.

558
00:40:46,910 --> 00:40:48,800
Once Thee finds a new assistant,

559
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:50,800
you guys can get back to your vacation.

560
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,100
Vacation’s over.

561
00:40:59,420 --> 00:41:00,800
Over?

562
00:41:03,780 --> 00:41:06,700
The schedule for the grand meeting
has been announced.

563
00:41:29,940 --> 00:41:31,000
Europe’s nice.

564
00:41:31,850 --> 00:41:32,900
I like the weather there.

565
00:41:33,430 --> 00:41:34,740
Asia’s boring.

566
00:41:34,760 --> 00:41:35,940
I’ve lived here my whole life.

567
00:41:37,160 --> 00:41:38,420
What about you, Mok?

568
00:41:39,830 --> 00:41:41,060
Just asking though.

569
00:41:41,260 --> 00:41:43,460
It’s not like we actually get to choose.

570
00:41:44,220 --> 00:41:46,060
If Mr. Thee gets to choose his own path,

571
00:41:46,900 --> 00:41:47,780
then you can—

572
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:48,620
No.

573
00:41:49,660 --> 00:41:50,700
Honestly,

574
00:41:52,380 --> 00:41:53,580
I think Kian’s job

575
00:41:58,380 --> 00:42:00,100
is even more boring than Dad’s.

576
00:42:08,330 --> 00:42:09,700
Why do you look like you don’t believe me?

577
00:42:09,780 --> 00:42:11,460
The three of us grew up together.

578
00:42:11,690 --> 00:42:12,500
But…

579
00:42:23,550 --> 00:42:25,350
When Mr. Thee was transferred to Thailand,

580
00:42:25,370 --> 00:42:28,980
you seemed so against
the decentralization strategy.

581
00:42:29,590 --> 00:42:32,100
Why do you seem okay with it now?

582
00:42:32,580 --> 00:42:33,430
I don’t get it.

583
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:34,700
Because it’s Kian.

584
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:39,300
Yes?

585
00:42:41,630 --> 00:42:43,330
I was upset with Dad then

586
00:42:43,710 --> 00:42:45,400
because he split us up.

587
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:47,300
That’s all.

588
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,000
Huh?

589
00:42:56,090 --> 00:42:57,150
People always say

590
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:59,200
I’m decisive, just like Dad.

591
00:43:00,460 --> 00:43:03,450
Kian’s gentle, just like Mom.

592
00:43:05,830 --> 00:43:06,800
What about you?

593
00:43:08,500 --> 00:43:09,500
Do you think so?

594
00:43:20,440 --> 00:43:23,130
So Mr. Rome’s being transferred
to the other side of the world?

595
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:25,500
It all depends on Dad.

596
00:43:28,230 --> 00:43:29,500
There’s no way to know.

597
00:43:35,670 --> 00:43:37,400
I’m going back to work tomorrow.

598
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,100
I’m interviewing a new assistant.

599
00:43:43,450 --> 00:43:45,040
Dad found you a new candidate?

600
00:43:47,180 --> 00:43:51,300
The sooner I find a new assistant,

601
00:43:53,350 --> 00:43:56,300
the longer Rome and Mok
can enjoy their lives

602
00:43:58,100 --> 00:43:59,600
before the grand meeting.

603
00:44:03,190 --> 00:44:05,000
Mr. Rome would be so happy

604
00:44:06,700 --> 00:44:09,220
to know how much
his big brother loves him.

605
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:16,000
Don’t you ever tell him.

606
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:18,810
He’ll never let me live it down.

607
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:30,800
They should be here any minute, sir.

608
00:44:44,910 --> 00:44:45,700
Good morning.

609
00:44:46,090 --> 00:44:47,300
I’m Mira.

610
00:44:47,870 --> 00:44:50,420
I’m ready to be
your new assistant, Mr. Theerakit.

611
00:45:01,390 --> 00:45:03,000
I owe you an apology, Mr. Thee.

612
00:45:04,460 --> 00:45:07,530
No one told me
your new assistant was a woman.

613
00:45:08,980 --> 00:45:10,000
I’m a woman.

614
00:45:10,870 --> 00:45:12,000
Is that a problem, sir?

615
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:15,940
Here’s the thing.

616
00:45:15,970 --> 00:45:19,900
Being his assistant means
helping with ARSENI’s business…

617
00:45:20,550 --> 00:45:21,940
and looking after his safety.

618
00:45:23,510 --> 00:45:25,650
I hope you understand
what I’m saying, Ms. Mira.

619
00:45:27,210 --> 00:45:28,200
Never mind.

620
00:45:28,550 --> 00:45:31,200
I don’t care whether
my assistant’s a man or a woman.

621
00:45:32,030 --> 00:45:32,900
Besides,

622
00:45:34,980 --> 00:45:36,340
I told you already, Mok.

623
00:45:37,280 --> 00:45:38,500
This is my turf.

624
00:45:39,690 --> 00:45:40,800
I’ll be safe.

625
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:42,960
Even so…

626
00:45:43,260 --> 00:45:44,600
I brought some food—Ow!

627
00:45:45,310 --> 00:45:45,900
Ow!

628
00:45:46,180 --> 00:45:46,900
Don’t!

629
00:45:47,180 --> 00:45:48,500
She’s my partner’s little sister!

630
00:45:51,710 --> 00:45:52,700
My apologies.

631
00:45:53,270 --> 00:45:54,730
It was pure instinct.

632
00:45:55,050 --> 00:45:56,020
I’m sorry, ma’am.

633
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:05,940
Feeling a little more at ease now, buddy?

634
00:46:30,310 --> 00:46:32,100
You’re absolutely pathetic.

635
00:46:32,330 --> 00:46:33,900
That’s rich coming from you.

636
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:36,910
You were getting eaten alive
by mosquitoes the other night.

637
00:46:38,560 --> 00:46:39,400
Lookpeach.

638
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:42,680
Have you made up your mind
about the new assistant?

639
00:46:42,710 --> 00:46:44,900
Can’t you at least
give me some time to decide?

640
00:46:52,350 --> 00:46:53,600
I want Mok back.

641
00:46:59,450 --> 00:47:00,500
Mr. Rome.

642
00:47:07,260 --> 00:47:09,800
We… should get going.

643
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:11,340
Please excuse us.

644
00:47:12,190 --> 00:47:13,870
If you two want more time together,

645
00:47:13,890 --> 00:47:16,600
stop pretending
to sleep in separate places.

646
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:22,140
Don’t sneak into my house
in the middle of the night like a thief.

647
00:47:23,710 --> 00:47:25,420
At this point, it’s public knowledge.

648
00:47:53,710 --> 00:47:54,500
805.

649
00:48:01,890 --> 00:48:03,500
Good thing he brought it up.

650
00:48:04,100 --> 00:48:06,900
You can just move in with me tonight.

651
00:48:07,230 --> 00:48:07,980
I’ll help.

652
00:48:10,870 --> 00:48:13,000
708, lead the way.

653
00:48:32,610 --> 00:48:35,400
(The big boss is coming to Thailand
to attend the meeting in person.)

654
00:48:40,590 --> 00:48:43,180
(I don’t know what’s going to happen,)

655
00:48:43,780 --> 00:48:46,540
(but this meeting is different.)

656
00:48:52,550 --> 00:48:54,500
(I’m sure everything will work out.)

657
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:18,740
(No matter what happens,)

658
00:49:18,970 --> 00:49:21,900
(know that
you’ll always have me, Mr. Rome.)

659
00:49:28,850 --> 00:49:29,600
Mr. Rome.

660
00:49:32,080 --> 00:49:33,000
What’s going on?

661
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:37,530
Where’s Mr. Rome being transferred to?

662
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:39,100
He’s not being transferred.

663
00:49:40,640 --> 00:49:45,100
Rome’s going to be ARSENI’s next leader,

664
00:49:46,820 --> 00:49:47,900
taking over from Dad.

665
00:49:59,580 --> 00:50:00,350
Okay.

666
00:50:13,260 --> 00:50:14,900
Mok called back.

667
00:50:16,910 --> 00:50:18,400
They’re together,

668
00:50:22,030 --> 00:50:23,780
but Rome isn’t ready to see anyone yet.

669
00:50:24,050 --> 00:50:26,100
Knowing they’re safe is enough.

670
00:50:37,310 --> 00:50:38,400
Don’t overthink it.

671
00:50:40,010 --> 00:50:41,300
It’s been a long day.

672
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:45,100
Come here.

673
00:50:46,050 --> 00:50:47,200
Let me give you a hug.

674
00:51:02,010 --> 00:51:03,900
I feel like I’ve failed.

675
00:51:06,230 --> 00:51:10,100
Everything I’ve done all this time…

676
00:51:11,870 --> 00:51:13,100
none of it worked.

677
00:51:15,570 --> 00:51:17,300
It’s selfishness.

678
00:51:20,060 --> 00:51:22,500
I’m forcing Rome to carry a burden
that should’ve been mine.

679
00:51:28,420 --> 00:51:29,400
P’Kian.

680
00:51:32,920 --> 00:51:35,460
I’m a terrible big brother,
aren’t I, Lookpeach?

681
00:51:45,070 --> 00:51:46,300
Don’t blame yourself.

682
00:51:48,930 --> 00:51:52,820
I’m sure Dad and Mr. Rome
don’t see it that way.

683
00:51:57,320 --> 00:51:59,800
Being ARSENI’s leader isn’t easy.

684
00:52:01,580 --> 00:52:05,000
It’s a thousand times harder than
being sent to run a branch.

685
00:52:05,390 --> 00:52:07,700
But I believe that
if Mr. Rome doesn’t want it,

686
00:52:11,260 --> 00:52:12,700
Dad won’t force him…

687
00:52:14,580 --> 00:52:17,020
and will give him
the same freedom he gave you.

688
00:52:20,860 --> 00:52:22,200
Dad’s ARSENI

689
00:52:23,770 --> 00:52:26,100
is like a tiger raised to be a warrior.

690
00:52:27,690 --> 00:52:28,800
Too fierce.

691
00:52:30,290 --> 00:52:33,200
Too dangerous
to be released back into the wild.

692
00:52:36,910 --> 00:52:41,900
So someone has to keep that tiger in check.

693
00:52:42,720 --> 00:52:44,200
It’s either Mr. Rome…

694
00:52:45,660 --> 00:52:47,020
or you, right, P’Kian?

695
00:52:52,640 --> 00:52:54,100
I can face anything

696
00:52:56,410 --> 00:52:58,400
as long as you’re by my side.

697
00:53:08,620 --> 00:53:10,800
I’ll do whatever it takes not to lose you.

698
00:53:14,460 --> 00:53:15,700
I know that.

699
00:53:19,270 --> 00:53:20,400
Better than anyone.

700
00:54:10,210 --> 00:54:11,050
P’Kian.

701
00:54:25,290 --> 00:54:26,200
I…

702
00:54:27,270 --> 00:54:28,800
I’ve finally gotten a grip, Lookpeach.

703
00:54:30,350 --> 00:54:33,140
Let’s save that
for when it really matters.

704
00:55:06,250 --> 00:55:10,600
♪ L'amour est un oiseau rebelle ♪

705
00:55:10,810 --> 00:55:15,400
♪ Que nul ne peut apprivoiser ♪

706
00:55:17,760 --> 00:55:18,400
Phew!

707
00:55:20,390 --> 00:55:21,400
Well? How was that?

708
00:55:21,710 --> 00:55:23,000
Did I sing nicely?

709
00:55:29,110 --> 00:55:32,540
Want me to give it a try?

710
00:55:33,130 --> 00:55:33,860
Good idea.

711
00:55:37,730 --> 00:55:41,400
♪ L'amour est un oiseau rebelle ♪

712
00:55:41,640 --> 00:55:46,380
♪ Que nul ne peut apprivoiser ♪

713
00:55:48,210 --> 00:55:49,060
Let’s try that again.

714
00:55:50,180 --> 00:55:51,340
♪ L'amour… ♪

715
00:55:51,830 --> 00:55:52,540
♪ Laaa… ♪

716
00:55:53,150 --> 00:55:54,540
♪ L'amour est… ♪

717
00:55:57,300 --> 00:56:01,460
♪ L'amour est un oiseau rebelle ♪

718
00:56:01,870 --> 00:56:07,400
♪ Que nul ne peut apprivoiser ♪

719
00:56:19,410 --> 00:56:20,610
Can you ask Dad for me, Kian?

720
00:56:21,470 --> 00:56:23,060
I want to stay here with you and Mok.

721
00:56:23,100 --> 00:56:24,800
Hi. Want to come in with me?

722
00:56:25,980 --> 00:56:26,750
Hey!

723
00:56:26,860 --> 00:56:28,700
I did something for Mr. Thee.

724
00:56:29,010 --> 00:56:30,100
You prepared a surprise for me?

725
00:56:31,100 --> 00:56:33,550
All my time belongs to you.

726
00:56:33,590 --> 00:56:34,770
We’re both going to work.

727
00:56:34,790 --> 00:56:35,680
And we’ll see each other this evening.

728
00:56:35,700 --> 00:56:37,100
Then let me get a refill first.

729
00:56:37,980 --> 00:56:42,100
Lookpeach, what would you say
if Dad’s position ended up being mine?

